---
import SiteLayout from "../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";

const schema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Article",
  "headline": "Fertility Window Calculator",
  "description": "Estimate your fertile window and ovulation day based on your menstrual cycle. Includes visual calendar.",
  "author": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "The Nookie Nook"
  },
  "mainEntity": {
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can I use this calculator as a form of birth control?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "No. This calculator provides estimates based on averages. Since cycles can fluctuate and sperm can live inside the body for up to 5 days, relying on calendar math alone is not a reliable method to prevent pregnancy."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "When does ovulation usually occur?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Ovulation typically occurs about 14 days before the start of your next period. However, this can vary significantly from person to person and month to month."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the fertile window?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "The fertile window includes the day of ovulation and the five days leading up to it, as sperm can survive in the reproductive tract for up to five days."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
};

export const meta = {
  title: "Interactive Fertility Window Calculator | The Nookie Nook",
  description: "Estimate your fertile window and ovulation day based on your menstrual cycle. Includes a visual calendar and evidence-based tips.",
  category: "tool",
  published: "2026-03-15",
};
---
<SiteLayout
  site="nookienook"
  title="Interactive Fertility Window Calculator | The Nookie Nook"
  description="Estimate your fertile window and ovulation day based on your menstrual cycle. Includes a visual calendar and evidence-based tips."
  canonical="https://thenookienook.com/fertility-window-calculator"
  schema={schema}
>
  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="hero">
      <h1>Fertility Window Calculator</h1>
      <p>Track your cycle and estimate your most fertile days.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="content-section">
      <div class="warning-banner">
        <strong>Important Disclaimer:</strong> This tool provides <em>estimates</em> based on statistical averages. It should <strong>not</strong> be used as a reliable method of contraception. If you are trying to avoid pregnancy, please use an established contraceptive method. See our <a href="/contraception-comparison">Contraception Comparison Tool</a> for options.
      </div>

      <div class="calculator-card">
        <form id="fertility-form" onsubmit="calculateFertility(event)">
          <div class="form-grid">
            <div class="input-group">
              <label for="last-period">First day of your last period:</label>
              <input type="date" id="last-period" required>
            </div>
            <div class="input-group">
              <label for="cycle-length">Average cycle length (days):</label>
              <input type="number" id="cycle-length" min="20" max="45" value="28" required>
              <div class="hint">Typically 28 days. Count from day 1 of a period to day 1 of the next.</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <button type="submit" class="calc-btn">Calculate Fertile Window</button>
        </form>

        <div id="calc-results" class="results-container" style="display: none;">
          <h3>Your Estimated Cycle Dates</h3>
          <div class="dates-grid">
            <div class="date-box highlight">
              <div class="date-label">Estimated Ovulation</div>
              <div class="date-value" id="res-ovulation">--</div>
            </div>
            <div class="date-box">
              <div class="date-label">Fertile Window Starts</div>
              <div class="date-value" id="res-fertile-start">--</div>
            </div>
            <div class="date-box">
              <div class="date-label">Fertile Window Ends</div>
              <div class="date-value" id="res-fertile-end">--</div>
            </div>
            <div class="date-box">
              <div class="date-label">Next Period Expected</div>
              <div class="date-value" id="res-next-period">--</div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="calendar-view" id="calendar-view">
            <!-- Calendar generated via JS -->
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2>Understanding the Fertile Window</h2>
      <p>Whether you are trying to conceive or simply want a better understanding of your body's natural rhythms, tracking your menstrual cycle is incredibly empowering. Part of our <a href="/sexual-health-guide">Comprehensive Sexual Health Guide</a>, this page explains the biology behind your cycle.</p>

      <h3>The Science of Conception</h3>
      <p>Pregnancy occurs when a sperm fertilizes an egg. For this to happen, intercourse must take place during a specific timeframe known as the "fertile window."</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Sperm Lifespan:</strong> Sperm can survive inside the female reproductive tract for up to <strong>5 days</strong> in the right conditions (specifically, in the presence of fertile cervical mucus).</li>
        <li><strong>Egg Lifespan:</strong> Once released during ovulation, an egg lives for only <strong>12 to 24 hours</strong>.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Because of these lifespans, the fertile window is generally considered to be the 5 days leading up to ovulation, plus the day of ovulation itself.</p>

      <h3>How to Track More Accurately</h3>
      <p>Calendar math is a good starting point, but bodies aren't machines. Stress, illness, travel, and routine changes can all delay or speed up ovulation. For more accurate tracking (known as Fertility Awareness Methods or FAM), look for physical signs:</p>
      <div class="card">
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Cervical Mucus:</strong> As you approach ovulation, estrogen levels rise, causing cervical mucus to become clear, slippery, and stretchy (often compared to raw egg whites). This mucus helps sperm survive and travel.</li>
          <li><strong>Basal Body Temperature (BBT):</strong> After ovulation occurs, a surge in progesterone causes a slight but measurable increase in your resting body temperature (about 0.5 to 1 degree Fahrenheit). You must measure this first thing in the morning before getting out of bed.</li>
          <li><strong>Ovulation Predictor Kits (OPKs):</strong> These over-the-counter urine tests detect a surge in Luteinizing Hormone (LH), which typically happens 24-36 hours before the egg is released.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <p>If you have questions about your cycle length or notice irregularities (like consistently missing periods or experiencing severe pain), it's a good idea to consult a healthcare provider. Check out our <a href="/guide-talking-to-doctor">Guide to Talking to Your Doctor</a> for tips on initiating that conversation.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <script is:inline>
    // Set default date to today
    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
      const today = new Date();
      document.getElementById('last-period').value = today.toISOString().split('T')[0];
    });

    function formatDate(date) {
      return date.toLocaleDateString('en-US', { weekday: 'short', month: 'short', day: 'numeric' });
    }

    function calculateFertility(e) {
      e.preventDefault();

      const lastPeriodStr = document.getElementById('last-period').value;
      const cycleLength = parseInt(document.getElementById('cycle-length').value, 10);

      if (!lastPeriodStr || isNaN(cycleLength)) return;

      // Ensure timezone consistency by parsing components
      const [year, month, day] = lastPeriodStr.split('-');
      const lastPeriodDate = new Date(year, month - 1, day);

      // Calculations
      // Luteal phase is generally 14 days for most people
      const lutealPhaseLength = 14;

      // Next period = last period + cycle length
      const nextPeriodDate = new Date(lastPeriodDate);
      nextPeriodDate.setDate(lastPeriodDate.getDate() + cycleLength);

      // Ovulation = next period - 14 days
      const ovulationDate = new Date(nextPeriodDate);
      ovulationDate.setDate(nextPeriodDate.getDate() - lutealPhaseLength);

      // Fertile window = 5 days before ovulation up to 1 day after
      const fertileStartDate = new Date(ovulationDate);
      fertileStartDate.setDate(ovulationDate.getDate() - 5);

      const fertileEndDate = new Date(ovulationDate);
      fertileEndDate.setDate(ovulationDate.getDate() + 1);

      // Update UI texts
      document.getElementById('res-ovulation').innerText = formatDate(ovulationDate);
      document.getElementById('res-fertile-start').innerText = formatDate(fertileStartDate);
      document.getElementById('res-fertile-end').innerText = formatDate(fertileEndDate);
      document.getElementById('res-next-period').innerText = formatDate(nextPeriodDate);

      // Generate Calendar
      generateCalendar(lastPeriodDate, fertileStartDate, fertileEndDate, ovulationDate, nextPeriodDate);

      document.getElementById('calc-results').style.display = 'block';
      document.getElementById('calc-results').scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth', block: 'nearest' });
    }

    function generateCalendar(periodStart, fertileStart, fertileEnd, ovulation, nextPeriod) {
      const container = document.getElementById('calendar-view');
      container.innerHTML = '';

      // Create a 35-day view starting from period start
      const calGrid = document.createElement('div');
      calGrid.className = 'cal-grid';

      for (let i = 0; i < 35; i++) {
        const currentDate = new Date(periodStart);
        currentDate.setDate(periodStart.getDate() + i);

        const dayBox = document.createElement('div');
        dayBox.className = 'cal-day';

        // Strip times for comparison
        const cTime = currentDate.getTime();
        const pStart = periodStart.getTime();
        const fStart = fertileStart.getTime();
        const fEnd = fertileEnd.getTime();
        const oTime = ovulation.getTime();
        const nPeriod = nextPeriod.getTime();

        let label = '';
        if (cTime >= pStart && cTime < pStart + (5 * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000)) {
          dayBox.classList.add('cal-period');
          if (cTime === pStart) label = 'Period Start';
        }

        if (cTime >= fStart && cTime <= fEnd) {
          dayBox.classList.add('cal-fertile');
          if (cTime === fStart) label = 'Fertile Window Begins';
        }

        if (cTime === oTime) {
          dayBox.classList.add('cal-ovulation');
          label = 'Estimated Ovulation';
        }

        if (cTime === nPeriod) {
          dayBox.classList.add('cal-next-period');
          label = 'Next Period';
        }

        dayBox.innerHTML = `
          <div class="cal-date-num">${currentDate.getDate()}</div>
          <div class="cal-month">${currentDate.toLocaleDateString('en-US', { month: 'short' })}</div>
          ${label ? `<div class="cal-label">${label}</div>` : ''}
        `;

        calGrid.appendChild(dayBox);

        // Stop rendering if we've passed the next period by a few days
        if (cTime > nPeriod + (3 * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000)) break;
      }

      // Add legend
      const legend = document.createElement('div');
      legend.className = 'cal-legend';
      legend.innerHTML = `
        <div class="legend-item"><span class="legend-color" style="background: rgba(232, 67, 147, 0.2); border-left-color: #E84393;"></span> Period</div>
        <div class="legend-item"><span class="legend-color" style="background: rgba(45, 184, 154, 0.15); border-left-color: #2DB89A;"></span> Fertile Window</div>
        <div class="legend-item"><span class="legend-color" style="background: #2DB89A;"></span> Ovulation</div>
      `;

      container.appendChild(legend);
      container.appendChild(calGrid);
    }
  </script>

  <style is:inline>
    .page-content { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1.5rem; }
    .hero { text-align: center; padding: 3rem 0 2rem; }
    .hero h1 { font-size: 2.2rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: var(--accent-color); }
    .hero p { color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 1.2rem; }

    .content-section { margin-bottom: 3rem; }
    .content-section h2 { font-size: 1.8rem; margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: var(--accent-color); }
    .content-section h3 { font-size: 1.3rem; margin-top: 1.5rem; color: var(--text-primary); }
    .content-section p { margin-bottom: 1.2rem; font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.7; }
    .content-section a { color: var(--accent-color); text-decoration: underline; }
    .content-section a:hover { color: var(--text-primary); }
    .content-section ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
    .content-section li { margin-bottom: 0.8rem; line-height: 1.6; }

    .warning-banner { background-color: rgba(224, 90, 90, 0.1); border-left: 4px solid #E05A5A; padding: 1rem 1.5rem; border-radius: 4px; margin-bottom: 2rem; color: var(--text-primary); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.5; }

    .card { background: var(--card-bg); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: 12px; padding: 2rem; margin: 2rem 0; }
    .card ul { margin-bottom: 0; }

    .calculator-card { background: var(--card-bg); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: 12px; padding: 2rem; margin: 2rem 0; box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.1); }
    .form-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
    @media (max-width: 600px) { .form-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }

    .input-group label { display: block; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-primary); }
    .input-group input { width: 100%; padding: 0.8rem; border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: 8px; background: var(--bg-color); color: var(--text-primary); font-family: var(--font-main); font-size: 1rem; }
    .input-group input:focus { outline: none; border-color: var(--accent-color); }
    .hint { font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--text-secondary); margin-top: 0.5rem; }

    .calc-btn { width: 100%; background: var(--accent-color); color: #fff; border: none; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 8px; font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 700; cursor: pointer; transition: opacity 0.2s; }
    .calc-btn:hover { opacity: 0.9; }

    .results-container { margin-top: 2rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding-top: 2rem; }
    .results-container h3 { text-align: center; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }

    .dates-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr)); gap: 1rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
    .date-box { background: var(--bg-color); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: 8px; padding: 1.2rem; text-align: center; }
    .date-box.highlight { border-color: #2DB89A; background: rgba(45, 184, 154, 0.05); }
    .date-label { color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px; }
    .date-value { color: var(--text-primary); font-size: 1.3rem; font-weight: 700; }
    .date-box.highlight .date-value { color: #2DB89A; }

    .calendar-view { margin-top: 2rem; }
    .cal-legend { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 1rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; justify-content: center; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--text-secondary); }
    .legend-item { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.4rem; }
    .legend-color { width: 16px; height: 16px; border-radius: 4px; border-left: 3px solid transparent; }

    .cal-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(7, 1fr); gap: 0.5rem; }
    @media (max-width: 768px) { .cal-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr); } }
    @media (max-width: 480px) { .cal-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); } }

    .cal-day { background: var(--bg-color); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: 6px; padding: 0.8rem 0.5rem; text-align: center; min-height: 80px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; justify-content: flex-start; }
    .cal-date-num { font-size: 1.2rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--text-primary); }
    .cal-month { font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--text-secondary); text-transform: uppercase; }
    .cal-label { font-size: 0.7rem; margin-top: auto; padding-top: 0.5rem; font-weight: 600; line-height: 1.1; }

    .cal-period { background: rgba(232, 67, 147, 0.1); border-left: 3px solid #E84393; }
    .cal-period .cal-label { color: #E84393; }

    .cal-fertile { background: rgba(45, 184, 154, 0.1); border-left: 3px solid #2DB89A; }
    .cal-fertile .cal-label { color: #2DB89A; }

    .cal-ovulation { background: rgba(45, 184, 154, 0.2); border: 2px solid #2DB89A; }
    .cal-ovulation .cal-label { color: #2DB89A; font-weight: 800; }

    .cal-next-period { border: 2px dashed #E84393; }
    .cal-next-period .cal-label { color: #E84393; }
  </style>
</SiteLayout>
